<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4259] Groovyc Ant task hard-codes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4259</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ant task for Groovy hard-codes the glob pattern &quot;*.groovy&quot; when searching for source files. This obviously doesn&apos;t work for those of us who use a different extension (like &quot;.g&quot;). I&apos;ve attached a patch that adds a property called &quot;scriptExtension&quot; to the task, which parallels GMaven&apos;s defaultScriptExtension property. This makes the extension configurable. It defaults to &quot;.groovy&quot; but can be changed if one uses something different.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
